  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header" style="margin-bottom: var(--s-6);"><div class="eyebrow">15 &middot; What commercial talent + Stairway coordination looks like</div><h2>Real-world commercial talent multi-source mortgage coordination.</h2>
      <p>A Tampa voiceover artist came to Stairway after prior generalist lender couldn&rsquo;t handle multi-source SAG-AFTRA W-2 session fees + residuals + buyouts + loan-out S-corp K-1 + non-union corporate 1099 synthesis with booking-variability smoothing. Client: $1.85M Tampa Hyde Park primary residence, voiceover artist with 19-year SAG-AFTRA membership + recurring national VO campaigns for insurance + automotive + fast food + technology + pharmaceutical advertisers. Home studio business operating through Voice Studios LLC (loan-out S-corp PLLC) with broadcast-quality booth + Neumann TLM microphones + Apollo Twin interface + ProTools workflow + soundproofing + acoustic treatment. Hybrid SAG-AFTRA + non-union work. Multi-source income structure: $385K W-2 session fees from SAG-AFTRA signatory production companies across recurring campaigns + $285K residuals (SAG-AFTRA Residuals administration documenting network + cable + web + foreign re-use) + $185K buyouts (lump-sum payments for digital + streaming + social commercial use) + $48K holding fees + $125K non-union corporate narration 1099 (medical pharmaceutical narration + e-learning + IVR systems) + $48K audiobook 1099 (publisher signatory work) + spouse $145K W-2 marketing executive at major Tampa advertising agency. Combined household $1.221M gross income. <strong>Multi-source coordination: W-2 session fees + residuals + buyouts + holding fees under B3-3.1-01 with 24-month averaging on booking-variability income. Loan-out S-corp K-1 under B3-3.4-02 with Form 1084 cash-flow analysis adding back $135K home studio (equipment + soundproofing + microphones + audio interface + acoustic treatment) + headshots + reels + demo production + agency commission (10% of bookings) + manager fees (10%) + entertainment attorney fees (5%) + audition expenses + casting workshops + acting classes + business travel + craft + ProTools subscriptions + research subscriptions + streaming subscriptions for business use. Non-union 1099 corporate narration + e-learning + audiobook under B3-3.2-01 with Schedule C + Form 1084 add-backs. SAG-AFTRA + 2023 strike + AI protections + digital replica consent context documented. Continuity narrative documenting 19-year SAG-AFTRA membership + recurring national VO campaign relationships + home studio business operation + hybrid SAG-AFTRA / non-union work portfolio.</strong> Reasonable compensation analysis confirming W-2/K-1 split appropriate (32% W-2 / 68% K-1 within reasonable compensation guidelines for top-tier commercial VO talent). FL no-state-income-tax preserves substantial qualifying — vs California (13.3%) saves $162K annually on combined $1.221M income; vs New York (10.9%) saves $133K annually. Multi-decade lifetime preservation $4M-$6M+. $1.85M Conventional Jumbo close in 45 days. <strong>The pattern: top-tier commercial VO talent brings multi-source SAG-AFTRA + loan-out + non-union complexity, Stairway brings B3-3.1-01 + B3-3.4-02 multi-entity Form 1084 + B3-3.2-01 + SAG-AFTRA framework + comprehensive commercial talent continuity narrative craft.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="pre-cta-photo"><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/2773498/pexels-photo-2773498.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1800" alt="House keys at commercial talent + Stairway closing" width="1400" height="700" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/1400x700/0A0E1A/E8EEFF/png?text=Commercial+Close';"><div class="pre-cta-photo-caption"><span class="label">45-day Tampa voiceover artist loan-out S-corp + residuals + buyouts Conventional Jumbo close &middot; Tampa, FL</span></div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

